Field names should comply with a naming convention
Why is this an issue? Sharing some naming conventions is a key point to make it possible for a team to efficiently collaborate. This rule allows to check that field names match a provided regular expression. 
### Noncompliant
class MyClass {
   private int my_field;
}
### Compliant
class MyClass {
   private int myField;
}
### Noncompliant
{{BUGGY}}
